# Rhino Player — Cursor / agent context (compact)

## Purpose

- **Rhino Player**: mpv-backed media player for Linux (GNOME, Ubuntu, and similar) with **GTK4 / libadwaita** UI, implemented in **Rust**, targeting a **statically linked** distributable when feasible.
- **Product context**: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md` (use cases and feature map). Behavior is specified in `docs/` first, then implemented. Copyright © 2026 Peter Adrianov; license `GPL-3.0-or-later` in root `LICENSE` / `COPYRIGHT` and the About dialog.

## Directories

- `build.rs` — Linux: embeds `DT_RUNPATH` for `/usr/local/lib/<multiarch>` and `/usr/local/lib` so a locally built `libmpv` (e.g. VapourSynth) is preferred over the distro copy without `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`. macOS: Homebrew **`lib`** search path for **`libmpv.dylib`**.
- `scripts/macos-dev-env.sh` — exports `PKG_CONFIG_PATH` and `PATH` for Homebrew GTK 4 / libadwaita before `cargo build` on macOS.
- `scripts/macos-build-app-bundle.sh` — **`Rhino Player.app`** (default `dist/macos/` via **`DEST_ROOT`**): copies release `rhino-player`, `packaging/macos/Info.plist.in` → `Contents/Info.plist` (bundle id `ch.rhino.RhinoPlayer`, viewer UTIs/extensions), **`AppIcon.icns`**, **`Resources/data/icons`** hicolor tree, **`Resources/share/rhino-player/vs`**.
- `scripts/build-deb.sh` — binary **`.deb`** into **`releases/`** by default (`OUTPUT=` override): `/usr` layout; runtime deps `libgtk-4-1`, `libadwaita-1-0`, `libmpv2 | libmpv1`.
- `scripts/stage-github-release.sh` — **GitHub Release staging**: on Linux runs **`build-deb.sh`**; on macOS builds **`Rhino Player.app`** in a temp dir then **`Rhino-Player-<ver>-macos-<arch>.zip`** into **`releases/`**. See **`releases/README.md`** (tracked); binaries under **`releases/`** are gitignored.
- `releases/` — **`README.md`** + **`github-release-<tag>.md`** (GitHub Release description templates) tracked; local `.deb` / `.zip` assets gitignored.
- `packaging/macos/` — **`Info.plist.in`** (`@VERSION@` from `Cargo.toml`); document types / icons for Finder integration.
- `data/` — Freedesktop assets: `data/icons` (hicolor app PNGs + `scalable/actions/speedometer-symbolic.svg`, `source/*` design + `rebuild-png-assets.sh`; see `data/icons/README.md`), `data/vs` (bundled `rhino_60_mvtools.vpy` — Linux loads `libmvtools.so`, macOS loads `libmvtools.dylib` via Homebrew; **HD**: native-decode MVTools **`FlowFPS`**; **UHD-class decode** (≥2560×1440): half-res **`FlowFPS`** output, no upscale; cached **`RHINO_MVTOOLS_LIB`** / `video_mvtools_lib`; [VapourSynth](https://www.vapoursynth.com/) notes: `data/vs/README.md`), `data/applications/*.desktop`, `data/metainfo` (AppStream), `install-to-user-dirs.sh` (installs to `~/.local/share` for shell/taskbar icon). Index: `data/README.md`.
- `docs/` — Feature specs **before** implementation. Index: `docs/README.md`. One file per feature area under `docs/features/`. Product and use cases: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md`. **`docs/screenshots/`** — numbered WebP for README / feature docs (`01-playback-main.webp`, `02-dvd-title-tracks.webp`, …).
- `doc/` — **`rhino-player.1`** man source (installed gzipped to **`share/man/man1/`** by **`install-system-wide.sh`** and the **`.deb`**).
- `src/` — `main.rs` (entry + locale), `lib.rs` (`mod mpris` — Linux-only MPRIS2 `mpris-server` + GTK main-context task; snapshots from transport), `sched.rs` (Linux `ioprio_set` I/O *class* best-effort at startup—no `nice`; from `main` before GTK), `app.rs` (thin include hub + `APP_ID`), `app/` (GTK shell split by responsibility: base/run, load, mpv realize, transport events (`observe_property` drain), final actions, input, file actions, file-loaded hooks, recent undo, chrome/open/seek/tooltip/`build_window` (main-window **`GdkFileList`/`GFile`** drop, same **`on_open`** as menu Open), `GtkWindowHandle` video move, bottom prev/play/next + seek + times + **Close Video**, header sound/sub/speed/menu popovers, preferences, session **Exit After Current Video**, `db::init`, EOF sibling advance), `audio_tracks.rs` (Sound popover → `playback_entity::audio_menu_rows`, `aid`), `sub_tracks.rs` (+ `sub_tracks_dvd.rs` → `sub_menu_rows`), `header_menu_scroll.rs` (Sound/Sub list scroll caps), `header_menu_tracks.rs` (rebuild audio/sub rows on menu open — windowed popover + macOS theater overlay), `icons.rs` (prepends **`Contents/Resources/data/icons`** inside a packaged `.app`, else **`CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR`/data/icons** for dev, so app id + bundled symbolics resolve), `db.rs` (SQLite `rhino.sqlite`: history, `settings` kv: `video_smooth_60` / `video_vs_path` / `video_mvtools_lib`, media duration/thumbs), `video_pref.rs` (optional VapourSynth `vf` from `db::VideoPrefs`, bundled `data/vs/rhino_60_mvtools.vpy`, `smooth_vf_swap_timing` + **`report_swap`** while Smooth vf is on, mvtools cache + `RHINO_MVTOOLS_LIB` from `paths::mvtools_from_env` / `mvtools_lib_search`, `RHINO_SOURCE_FPS` from mpv `container-fps` so the script recovers cadence when mpv passes `0/0`), `mpv_embed.rs` + `mpv_embed/` (Linux: libmpv `RenderContext` bound to a [`gtk::GLArea`] via `gl_platform.rs` (EGL/GL `dlsym`); macOS: native [`CAOpenGLLayer`] inserted **directly as a sublayer of the NSWindow contentView's `layer`** — gdk-macos renders GTK widgets straight into that contentView layer with no NSView subviews of its own, so an NSView wrapper for our layer would never composite (`drawInCGLContext:` fires but nothing reaches the screen); the `CAOpenGLLayer` is driven by a [`CVDisplayLink`] running on its own kernel thread so AppKit menu / popover tracking on the main run loop cannot stall video — `macos_video_cgl` (CGL pixel format + context, `OpenGL.framework` symbol loader), `macos_video_layer` (`RhinoMpvGlLayer : CAOpenGLLayer` subclass with `copyCGLContext:` / `drawInCGLContext:` overrides; `display_now()` just calls `setNeedsDisplay` so CA can pick up the frame in `kCFRunLoopCommonModes`), `macos_video_attach` (set `contentView.wantsLayer=true`, `insertSublayer:atIndex:0` so the native layer sits *under* gdk-macos's GTK rendering sublayer — combined with the **transparent GLArea** trick (`.rp-gl-native` CSS background + alpha-0 GL clear in the GLArea's render callback, see `MpvBundle::clear_glarea_transparent`) the GLArea region of gdk's sublayer is alpha=0 so the video below shows through, while opaque chrome (header / bottom bar) stays visible on top; own the displayLink; `watch_overlay` registers a GTK widget — typically the recent grid — and `setHidden:` flips so the grid is visible whenever the layer would otherwise cover it; per-frame layer-frame mirroring (GTK widget allocation → Cocoa-coords `setFrame:` / `setBounds:` / `setHidden:` under `CATransaction(setDisableActions:true)`) lives in the sibling `macos_video_layer_frame` module, called from `connect_realize` + `add_tick_callback`), `macos_video_displaylink` (`CVDisplayLinkCreateWithActiveCGDisplays` + output callback that consumes a coalescing `AtomicBool` and calls `RhinoMpvGlLayer::display_now`), `macos_video_bundle` (mpv render context — update callback marks the displayLink pending, draw closure calls `mpv_render_context_render` from inside `drawInCGLContext:` with the layer's bound FBO + `MPV_RENDER_PARAM_FLIP_Y`; also exposes `clear_glarea_transparent` which reuses the bundle's own `OpenGL.framework` handle instead of opening a second one); `linux_egl_helpers.rs` carries the cross-platform `EglState` / `egl_proc` / `GL_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING` used by the Linux render path **and** the seek-bar preview's `MpvPreviewGl` on both OSes; `mpv_persistence.rs` carries the `MpvBundle` save / load / resume / `commit_quit` impl block included alongside the platform-shaped construction code), `idle_inhibit.rs` (GTK `Application::inhibit` IDLE+SUSPEND when playing, recent grid hidden; clear on quit), `paths.rs` (XDG config, mpv `watch_later`, bundled `.vpy` via dev tree / `PREFIX/share` / **`Contents/Resources/share` in `.app`**, icon theme **`Contents/Resources/data/icons`**; mvtools discovery — Linux: distro `vapoursynth/` + pipx vsrepo; macOS: Homebrew `lib/libmvtools.dylib`), `history.rs` (recent list via `db`), `human_media_title.rs` + `human_media_title/` (Transmission-like basename cleanup for window title, continue grid labels, Linux MPRIS filename fallback when `media-title` is empty), `media_probe.rs` (`remove_continue_entry` = resume clear + history remove, card data, libmpv `vo=image` + quit thumb for DB), `seek_bar_preview.rs` (popover + time; 2nd libmpv + small `GLArea` / `MpvPreviewGl` like the main [embed]), `jpeg_texture.rs` (JPEG → `GdkTexture` for recent grid; not `Texture::from_bytes` for raw bytes), `continue_undo.rs` (session snackbar **Undo**: list-remove vs **trash** + untrash), `trash_xdg.rs` (Freedesktop `Trash` locate + restore from `files/`), `sibling_advance.rs` (next/prev local file in folder + sibling order; EOF + bottom bar), `playback_entity.rs` (+ `playback_entity_tracks.rs` IFO title-set Sound/Sub rows; `playback_entity_title.rs` window title; `playback_entity_persist.rs`, `playback_entity_dvd_card.rs`; one logical title: single file or multi-part DVD — history/resume DB key), `dvd_entity.rs` (one SQLite/history row per `VTS_XX_*` title; global resume/duration), `dvd_vob_ffprobe.rs` (`ffprobe` per queued `.vob`, session cache), `dvd_vob_timeline.rs` (+ `dvd_vob_chapter_marks.rs`, `dvd_vob_bar.rs`, `dvd_vob_timeline_transport.rs`, `dvd_chapter_eof.rs`; `dvd_entity_timeline.rs` in `dvd_entity.rs` — VOB queue + per-file durations for seek/EOF; IFO PTT labels for marks only; feature 30), `dvd_ifo_parse.rs` (`VIDEO_TS.IFO` main-title pick + `VTS_xx_0.IFO` PTT marks + audio/sub attrs), `video_ext.rs` (shared `SUFFIX` for **Open** + siblings; **BDMV** / **VIDEO_TS** disc roots), `macos_header_menu.rs` + `macos_header_menu_overlay.rs` (macOS: windowed opaque GtkPopover; theater **`outer_ovl`** child reparent, popover detach, **`rp-header-menu-fs`** — `docs/references-gtk4-macos-header-menus.md`)), `macos_open_video.rs` (macOS `NSOpenPanel` + `setAllowedContentTypes`), `recent_view.rs` (continue grid, card hover: **trash** + **remove**, spacer `dbl`→fullscreen, session undo), `time.rs` (time formatting + tests), `playback_speed.rs` (1.0/1.5/2.0/8.0× + mpv `speed` sync for header `ListBox`), `theme.rs` (CSS: dark chrome + `cursor: pointer` / `not-allowed` on controls; see `.cursor/rules/ui-cursor.mdc`), `macos_window.rs` (one shared `nswindow_for_widget` helper resolving the `NSWindow` for a `gtk::Widget` via `gdk4_macos`, used by traffic-lights + the native-video attach module; toggles the standard traffic-light buttons through `NSWindow::standardWindowButton` because GTK's `set_show_*_title_buttons` is one-way on macOS).
- `tests/` — Integration tests (e.g. libmpv smoke).

## Workflow

- **Document-first**: see `.cursor/rules/document-first.mdc`. **`Notes`/`data/*/README`** avoid duplicating tuning literals from Rust/`.vpy` — cite symbols instead (`.cursor/rules/docs-no-mirrored-tuning.mdc`). Three layers (see `docs/architecture.md`): **product behavior** (feature scenarios — portable), **architecture core** (fixed: Rust, SQLite, mpv), **platform binding** (varies per port — today: Linux / GTK / libadwaita / XDG). Each `docs/features/<NN>-<slug>.md` follows the strict template — H1, YAML front-matter (`status`, `priority`, `layers`, optional `related` / `scope`), `## Use cases`, `## Description`, `## Behavior` (single `Feature:` Gherkin block in domain language only — the single source of truth for acceptance), optional `## Notes` (the **only** place for engine APIs, UI-toolkit widgets, OS paths, env vars, persistence schema, and language types). Layer vocabulary: `ui`, `input`, `playback`, `persistence`, `storage`, `os-integration`, `build`.
- **Known UX not achieved in testing (Composer 2 Fast pass):** one-click switch between header `MenuButton` popovers — see `docs/README.md` (*Tooling note*) and `docs/features/17-window-behavior.md`. Revisit with a different model or deeper GTK review.

## Conventions

- Keep `.cursorrules` and `docs/README.md` feature list aligned with what exists in the tree.
- Prefer clear module boundaries: UI (GTK/Adwaita), mpv control, platform (DBus, portals), persistence (settings, session).
- **Quality checks:** run `cargo qcheck` (Clippy across the whole crate) before finishing. Module length is policed by `clippy::too_many_lines` (warns over ~300 lines) plus `.cursor/rules/refactor-touched-longest.mdc` (every request that edits an oversized module must shrink it in the same turn). Do not add `#[allow(clippy::…)]`—fix by refactoring (see `.cursor/rules/clippy-no-suppress.mdc`). If many modules exceed the soft limit, refactor **one file at a time**, **longest first**.
- **Six-file scatter rule:** one behavior change touching **more than six production files** (see count table in `.cursor/rules/complexity-and-module-design.mdc`) → **mandatory consolidation** in the same workstream: one module owns the feature, dependents call a narrow API — do not ship scattered hooks. Clippy + soft **~300 lines**/file: `clippy.toml`, `refactor-touched-longest.mdc`.
- **UI / IO timing:** prefer event subscriptions over periodic polls; see `.cursor/rules/events-over-polling.mdc`.
- Name length: prefer short, clear identifiers (2–3 words) for new types and functions, consistent with the rest of the file.
